  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Neha, it's been a while — I hope your walk and palette work are done by now!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Palette? Oh, you mean palette... no, that was a while back. Just... done with it. Bored now. Walked a lot, though. Found a new cafe. Maybe you’d like it."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Found a new cafe! That sounds fun. Was it near your apartment? What made you go there?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No, it wasn’t near my apartment. I was walking somewhere, got thirsty, and saw the board. The name was cute — “Velvet Bean”. Walked in. Coffee was alright, but the cake… mmm. Not sure if I’ll go again. The vibe was too chill for me."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Ah, 'Velvet Bean' — what a lovely name! The cake sounds tempting. Do you usually prefer a busier or quieter place when you go out?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm. I like quiet, but not too quiet. If it’s too chill, I get antsy. Maybe a bit of background noise, like soft music or people chatting low. You know, the kind of place where you can focus but still feel alive. Like… not a library, but not a club either."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — a happy middle, not too still, not too loud. What kind of music would you want playing in that perfect spot?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Indie folk, maybe a bit of lo-fi. Something that doesn’t demand attention but adds to the mood. No lyrics, or just soft ones. You know, the kind of music that fades into the background but still feels like it belongs there. Like… if the walls could hum."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — music that blends into the space, not the other way around. What’s your go-to song for that kind of vibe?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "“Fools” by Radiohead. Not the whole album, just that one track. Or maybe “The A Team” by Ed Sheeran — the slow one. Wait, no… that’s too sad. Maybe “Ho Hey” by The Lumineers. You know, the one that’s just… there."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — music that's gently there. 'Ho Hey' fits exactly. What made you choose that kind of vibe today?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No energy for loud stuff today. Just feel like everything’s… heavy. Need something soft to float through it. Maybe I’ll put on “Ho Hey” later and pretend I’m in that cafe again. But not too long — I’ll get restless. Chai might be better."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Chai can be the perfect match for that quiet moment. One *chokli chokli* sip and the world feels softer. What kind of chai — cardamom, cinnamon, or plain?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Cardamom, of course. But not too much — I like a hint, not a hit. Sometimes, I add a pinch of cinnamon too. But mostly, I just want the warmth without the sweetness. Less sugar, more soul. Though today, maybe even that feels like work."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Cardamom with a soul — that’s a perfect mix. Some days, even tea feels like too much effort. What’s your go-to when you want to rest but still feel a little comfort?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "A thick blanket, old movie, and the click of the kettle in the background. Nothing loud, nothing demanding. Just enough to say, “you’re here, and that’s okay.” Sometimes I leave the lights low and let the shadows do the rest. But yeah, even that feels like work today."
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — quiet comfort, but not much effort. Some days, even that feels heavy. What’s one small thing that might feel easier than the rest?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "One small thing? A long stretch on the couch, hands behind my head, and the hum of a fan. Just… existing without a plan. Even that feels too big today, though. Maybe just existing."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Existing without a plan — that’s a real luxury. Even existing feels like a lot sometimes. What helps you take that first step when everything feels too much?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Just breathing, I guess. Or pretending to. Sometimes I’ll lie there and count the ceiling tiles until it feels like I’m doing something. Once I’m there, the rest comes slowly. But today… today I’m still counting."
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Counting ceiling tiles — a small act with big comfort. It’s okay to stay there as long as you need. What helps you feel ready to move when you’re ready?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "A soft chime, maybe a song that hums in the background… or a cup of chai that’s just warm enough. When I’m ready, I want the world to feel gentle, not pushy. Like it’s saying, “Take your time,” not “Hurry up.” But until then, I’ll keep counting tiles. One by one."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Tiles one by one — a quiet rhythm to match the day. A world that says 'Take your time' sounds like exactly what's needed. What’s the next tile counting into?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The next tile? Maybe the next cup of chai, or the next breath that doesn’t feel like effort. Or just… the next minute that passes quietly. Not sure yet. But for now, I’ll stay here."
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Staying here is perfectly okay. The next minute, the next breath — they’ll come when you’re ready. What’s been the quietest comfort for you so far today?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The quietest comfort? Maybe the silence between the fan’s hum and the kettle’s click. Or the moment before I take a sip of chai — when everything just… pauses. Like the world’s holding its breath with me. That’s it. That pause. So small, but enough."
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Such a small pause — but enough. The world holding its breath with you is a gentle thing. What’s one more tiny thing that could join in today?\""
    }
  ],
